<h1>LG Washer Motor Replacement</h1>

<p>An LG washer that won't spin or agitate and throws an LE or CE code can come down to the drive motor — though on LG's direct-drive machines it's often the hall sensor or a connector before it's the motor itself, and we check that first so you're not paying for a motor you don't need. When it is the motor, we replace it same-day across LA, $380–480 with OEM parts and a one-year warranty. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>Signs of a Failing LG Washer Motor</h2>
<p>A failing motor leaves the drum unable to spin or agitate, often with an <a href="/washer/error-codes/lg-washer-le-error/">LE code</a> for a locked or stalled motor, or a <a href="/washer/error-codes/lg-washer-ce-error/">CE code</a> for an overcurrent fault. You might catch a burning smell, or the washer may start and then stop under load. These same symptoms show up as an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-not-spinning/">LG washer that won't spin</a> — so before condemning the motor, we test the windings and the hall sensor, because the sensor fails far more often than the motor on these machines.</p>

<h2>How We Replace the Motor</h2>
<p>On LG's direct-drive design the motor is the rotor and stator at the back of the tub. Our techs test the rotor, stator windings, and hall sensor to pinpoint the actual fault. If it's genuinely the motor, we remove the rotor and stator and fit an OEM assembly, about a 1.5–2.5 hour job. Plenty of "dead motor" calls turn out to be a $250–320 hall sensor instead, which is exactly why we test before we order parts.</p>

<h2>Cost of Motor Replacement</h2>
<p>A full motor replacement runs $380–480 installed with OEM parts, and less when the fault is just the hall sensor. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. For the full breakdown of motor versus sensor pricing, see our <a href="/washer/price-list/lg-washer-motor-replacement-cost/">LG washer motor replacement cost</a> page.</p>

<h2>Motor vs a New Machine</h2>
<p>At $380–480 a motor replacement stays under the $800–1,500 a comparable new LG washer costs delivered and installed, so on a machine that's otherwise solid it's usually worth doing. If the washer is older and other major parts are wearing out alongside the motor, we'll give you an honest read on whether to repair or replace rather than sink a big repair into a machine near the end of its life.</p>

<h2>OEM Parts and Warranty</h2>
<p>We fit OEM motors and sensors, not generic substitutes, and back the work with a one-year warranty on parts and labor. There's no surcharge for same-day or weekend service.</p>

<p>No-spin or an LE code? Our LG Dryer Repair techs test the motor and sensor on-site across LA, Orange County, and Ventura County before quoting a part. Call (323) 990-7550; the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Motor Replacement</h2>

<h3>How do I know if my LG washer motor is bad?</h3>
<p>A failing LG washer motor won't spin or agitate, often throws an LE or CE code, and may give off a burning smell or stop under load. But on LG's direct-drive machines the hall sensor fails far more often than the motor, so those symptoms don't automatically mean a new motor.</p>

<h3>How much does LG washer motor replacement cost?</h3>
<p>A full motor replacement runs $380–480 installed with OEM parts; if the fault is just the hall sensor, it's $250–320 instead. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair, and the work has a one-year warranty. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Is it the motor or the hall sensor on my LG washer?</h3>
<p>Often it's the hall sensor, not the motor — the sensor tells the control where the rotor is, and when it fails the washer reads the motor as dead or locked (an LE code) even though the motor is fine. We test the sensor and the motor windings directly so you only pay for the part that actually failed.</p>

<h3>Is replacing an LG washer motor worth it?</h3>
<p>At $380–480 it's still below the $800–1,500 cost of a new LG washer, so on a machine that's otherwise solid it's usually worth it. If the washer is older and other major parts are wearing out, we'll give you an honest read on whether to repair or replace.</p>

<h3>How long does LG washer motor replacement take?</h3>
<p>A motor replacement on an LG direct-drive washer takes about 1.5–2.5 hours, and we do it same-day in most cases. We test the rotor, stator, and hall sensor first, then replace and test before we leave.</p>

